That was my original intention.  That was my &quot;big secret idea&quot; as referenced on page 1 of this thread.  However...<br>
<br>
1) Srir is now well aware of this situation, and may even have read this thread, and while he is dispicable, he is by no means stupid.  I am certain he will not give me the opportunity.<br>
<br>
2) I realize that as an unintended consequence of persuing his dishonestly so vigorously is that my own actions are now also scrutinized, and so I must be doing anything I do cleaner, and more &quot;by the rules&quot; than I ever have before.  At the risk of my own credibility, I cannot allow any ammunition Srir might use against me in a /petition or /report.  This means I cannot train on him, I cannot stalk him, I cannot entrap him.  All I can do (and all I WILL do anymore) is warn others of his treachery and deceit, all the while leading by example as to how an honorable character behaves.<br>
<br>
I am not, by a long shot, perfect.  But I must make clear the contrast between honorable behavior and the underhanded double-dealings of a dung-dipped skunk.<br>
<br>
However, observing and reporting the truth are both honorable and informative, and I will continue to do so.  It has now been several days since I have informed his current guild of this situation.  Wednsday of next week, I will reveal his guild, as I feel this gives them ample time to decide whether or not they will accept him &quot;with all faults&quot; into their fold, and if they choose to do so, then they also accept the stigma of having their name published here, along with a screenshot (and if Srir is anonymous, the Screenshot will also have a /time and /guildstatus as legible as it can be as part of that screenshot) so there is no question as to the truthfulness of my observation.<br>
<br>
I realize that Srir cares nothing for his reputation, but I care greatly about mine.  Observations from strangers have been that I am vindictive and vicious, with this thread being my only defense for the length and depth of my actions.  I feel they are fully justified.<br>
<br>
I feel that I am neither.  I am just.  I was wronged.  Others were wronged.  Let the hammer of justice fall heavily upon Srir and all who would harbor him.<br>
